<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 17 
                    President Truman to Prime Minister Churchill
                    
                    Presumably sent to the United States Naval Attaché,
                        London, via Navy channels.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d17</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">17</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-05-21T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 17 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_THS1" type="from">Truman</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CMWS1" type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d17fn1">Presumably sent to the United States Naval Attaché,
                        London, via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="2" xml:id="d17fn2">The portion of
                            this message not printed here related to Venezia Giulia. See <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>, <hi rend="italic">Year of
                                Decisions</hi>, pp. 250–251.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-21">21 May
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Your number 53. …<note n="3" xml:id="d17fn3">
                        <ref target="#d16">document No. 16</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I may, within the next two weeks, have more information bearing on a date and
                    location for the proposed tripartite meeting if <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2">Stalin</persName> agrees to participate.</p>
                <p>I hope he will agree to come west into Germany or further west, but I am advised
                    that he is not likely to go beyond Soviet controlled, territory.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
